INSERT INTO `vocabulary_word` VALUES (1,'allocate','할당하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The company allocated funds to research.','회사는 연구에 자금을 할당했다.'),(2,'substantially','상당히','adverb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Sales increased substantially last year.','지난해 매출이 상당히 증가했다.'),(3,'enforce','시행하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The government enforces strict laws.','정부는 엄격한 법을 시행한다.'),(4,'mandatory','의무적인','adjective','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Attending the seminar is mandatory.','세미나 참석은 의무다.'),(5,'terminate','종료하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The contract was terminated early.','계약은 조기에 종료되었다.'),(6,'reimbursement','환급, 상환','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','You can request reimbursement for travel costs.','출장비에 대해 환급을 요청할 수 있습니다.'),(7,'depreciation','가치 하락, 감가상각','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The car suffered from rapid depreciation.','그 차량은 빠른 감가상각을 겪었다.'),(8,'liability','법적 책임','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The company has no liability in this case.','이 사건에 대해 회사는 책임이 없다.'),(9,'comply','따르다, 준수하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Vendors must comply with safety standards.','공급업체는 안전 기준을 준수해야 한다.'),(10,'amend','수정하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The policy was amended to include new rules.','새로운 규칙이 포함되도록 정책이 수정되었다.'),(11,'acquisition','인수, 획득','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The acquisition of the company was completed.','회사 인수가 완료되었다.'),(12,'appraisal','평가','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','An annual performance appraisal is required.','연간 성과 평가는 필수다.'),(13,'deliberation','숙고, 토의','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','After much deliberation, they made a decision.','많은 숙고 끝에 그들은 결정을 내렸다.'),(14,'compensation','보상','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He received compensation for the damages.','그는 손해에 대한 보상을 받았다.'),(15,'compliance','준수','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Compliance with regulations is essential.','규정 준수는 필수적이다.'),(16,'proficiency','능숙','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Proficiency in English is required.','영어 능숙도가 요구된다.'),(17,'subsidiary','자회사','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The company opened a new subsidiary in Japan.','회사는 일본에 새로운 자회사를 설립했다.'),(18,'renovation','개조, 리노베이션','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The building is under renovation.','건물이 리노베이션 중이다.'),(19,'endorsement','지지, 승인','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The product received celebrity endorsement.','그 제품은 유명인의 지지를 받았다.'),(20,'contingency','비상사태, 우발 상황','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','We have a contingency plan in place.','우리는 비상 계획을 마련해 두었다.'),(21,'discretion','재량, 신중함','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The decision is at the manager\'s discretion.','그 결정은 매니저의 재량에 달려 있다.'),(22,'facilitate','촉진하다, 용이하게 하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The app facilitates communication.','그 앱은 의사소통을 용이하게 한다.'),(23,'consolidate','통합하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','They consolidated all the branches.','그들은 모든 지점을 통합했다.'),(24,'audit','회계 감사','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The company passed the financial audit.','회사는 재무 감사에 통과했다.'),(25,'expenditure','지출','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The government reduced public expenditure.','정부는 공공 지출을 줄였다.'),(26,'sustainability','지속 가능성','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The company focuses on sustainability.','그 회사는 지속 가능성에 중점을 둔다.'),(27,'insight','통찰력','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She has great insight into the market.','그녀는 시장에 대한 훌륭한 통찰력을 가지고 있다.'),(28,'authorize','인가하다, 권한을 부여하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He is authorized to sign the contract.','그는 계약을 체결할 권한이 있다.'),(29,'resign','사직하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She resigned from her position.','그녀는 직책에서 사임했다.'),(30,'strategic','전략적인','adjective','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The decision was strategic.','그 결정은 전략적이었다.'),(31,'collaborate','협력하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The two teams collaborated on the project.','두 팀은 프로젝트에서 협력했다.'),(32,'restructure','구조를 재조정하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The company restructured its departments.','회사는 부서를 재구성했다.'),(33,'curtail','삭감하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','They curtailed unnecessary expenses.','그들은 불필요한 지출을 삭감했다.'),(34,'outsource','외부에 위탁하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','We outsourced our IT support.','우리는 IT 지원을 외부에 위탁했다.'),(35,'speculate','추측하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Investors speculated on the market crash.','투자자들은 시장 붕괴를 추측했다.'),(36,'deteriorate','악화되다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','His health deteriorated rapidly.','그의 건강은 빠르게 악화되었다.'),(37,'stipulate','명시하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The contract stipulates the deadline.','계약은 마감일을 명시하고 있다.'),(38,'forecast','예측하다','verb','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The sales forecast looks promising.','판매 예측은 유망하게 보인다.'),(39,'recession','경기 침체','noun','hard','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The country is facing a recession.','그 나라는 경기 침체를 겪고 있다.'),(40,'basic','기본적인','adjective','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She has a basic understanding of English grammar.','그녀는 영어 문법에 대한 기본적인 이해를 가지고 있다.'),(41,'clean','깨끗한, 청소하다','adjective/verb','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Please clean your room before dinner.','저녁 식사 전에 방을 청소해 주세요.'),(42,'fast','빠른','adjective','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He runs very fast.','그는 매우 빠르게 달린다.'),(43,'food','음식','noun','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The restaurant serves delicious food.','그 식당은 맛있는 음식을 제공한다.'),(44,'happy','행복한','adjective','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She looks very happy today.','그녀는 오늘 매우 행복해 보인다.'),(45,'help','돕다','verb','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Can you help me with this box?','이 상자 좀 도와줄 수 있니?'),(46,'hot','뜨거운','adjective','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The soup is very hot.','그 수프는 매우 뜨겁다.'),(47,'job','직업, 일','noun','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He got a new job last week.','그는 지난주에 새 직장을 얻었다.'),(48,'like','좋아하다','verb','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','I like watching movies on weekends.','나는 주말에 영화를 보는 것을 좋아한다.'),(49,'look','보다, ~처럼 보이다','verb','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','You look tired today.','너 오늘 피곤해 보여.'),(50,'open','열다, 열린','verb/adjective','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Please open the window.','창문을 열어 주세요.'),(51,'phone','전화','noun','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','I forgot my phone at home.','나는 집에 전화를 두고 왔다.'),(52,'small','작은','adjective','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She has a small dog.','그녀는 작은 개를 키운다.'),(53,'stop','멈추다','verb','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Please stop talking.','말을 멈춰 주세요.'),(54,'work','일하다, 일','verb/noun','easy','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He works in an office.','그는 사무실에서 일한다.'),(55,'manage','관리하다, 경영하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She manages a team of five engineers.','그녀는 다섯 명의 엔지니어 팀을 관리한다.'),(56,'requirement','요구사항, 필요조건','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','A degree is a basic requirement for this job.','이 일자리는 학위가 기본적인 요구사항이다.'),(57,'candidate','지원자, 후보자','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','There are three candidates for the position.','그 직책에는 세 명의 후보자가 있다.'),(58,'reference','추천서, 참조','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Please include at least one reference with your application.','지원서에 최소한 하나의 추천서를 포함해 주세요.'),(59,'eligible','자격이 있는','adjective','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Only eligible members can vote.','자격이 있는 회원만 투표할 수 있다.'),(60,'associate','연관짓다, 동료','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','I always associate summer with the beach.','나는 여름을 해변과 연관지어 생각한다.'),(61,'apprehensive','걱정하는, 염려하는','adjective','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He felt apprehensive about the interview.','그는 면접에 대해 걱정스러워했다.'),(62,'entitle','자격을 주다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','You are entitled to a free drink.','당신은 무료 음료를 받을 자격이 있다.'),(63,'certification','자격증, 증명서','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She received a certification in project management.','그녀는 프로젝트 관리 자격증을 받았다.'),(64,'policy','정책, 방침','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The return policy is printed on the receipt.','환불 정책은 영수증에 인쇄되어 있다.'),(65,'comply','따르다, 준수하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Employees must comply with company rules.','직원들은 회사 규정을 준수해야 한다.'),(66,'regulation','규정','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The new regulation affects all businesses.','새로운 규정은 모든 사업체에 영향을 미친다.'),(67,'approval','승인','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','We need your approval to proceed.','우리는 진행을 위해 당신의 승인이 필요하다.'),(68,'procedure','절차','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Follow the procedure carefully.','절차를 신중히 따르세요.'),(69,'supervision','감독','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The project was completed under close supervision.','그 프로젝트는 철저한 감독하에 완료되었다.'),(70,'acquaint','익숙하게 하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Please acquaint yourself with the rules.','규칙에 익숙해지도록 하세요.'),(71,'submit','제출하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','Please submit your report by Friday.','보고서를 금요일까지 제출해 주세요.'),(72,'monitor','감시하다, 관찰하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','We monitor performance monthly.','우리는 매달 성과를 감시한다.'),(73,'assignment','과제, 임무','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','This is your next assignment.','이것이 당신의 다음 과제이다.'),(74,'candidate','지원자','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The candidate gave a strong impression.','지원자는 강한 인상을 주었다.'),(75,'responsible','책임이 있는','adjective','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She is responsible for the budget.','그녀는 예산을 책임지고 있다.'),(76,'conduct','수행하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','We will conduct an investigation.','우리는 조사를 실시할 것이다.'),(77,'supervise','감독하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He supervises the sales team.','그는 영업팀을 감독한다.'),(78,'coworker','동료','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','I had lunch with my coworker.','나는 동료와 점심을 먹었다.'),(79,'assign','배정하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The manager assigned me a new task.','매니저가 나에게 새 작업을 배정했다.'),(80,'formal','형식적인','adjective','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','The event is very formal.','그 행사는 매우 형식적이다.'),(81,'coordinate','조정하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','They coordinated the project together.','그들은 프로젝트를 함께 조정했다.'),(82,'accountable','책임이 있는','adjective','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','You are accountable for your actions.','당신은 자신의 행동에 책임이 있다.'),(83,'proficient','능숙한','adjective','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He is proficient in three languages.','그는 세 개 언어에 능숙하다.'),(84,'specialize','전문으로 하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','She specializes in civil law.','그녀는 민법을 전문으로 한다.'),(85,'familiar','익숙한','adjective','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','I\'m familiar with this software.','나는 이 소프트웨어에 익숙하다.'),(86,'conference','회의','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','We have a conference next week.','다음 주에 회의가 있다.'),(87,'promotion','승진, 판촉','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','He got a promotion last month.','그는 지난달 승진했다.'),(88,'evaluate','평가하다','verb','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','We need to evaluate the results.','결과를 평가해야 한다.'),(89,'strategy','전략','noun','medium','2025-03-21 17:45:44.000000','